The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 18, 2004 				 Philips unveils mirror TV
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Feb. 17: Dutch major Philips India Limited today launched a range of products, including a 23-inch mirror LCD TV at a price tag of Rs 1.79 lakh and a 30-inch flat LCD TV priced at a staggering Rs 2.29 lakh. 																								Designed as a multi-utility television set, the TV can be used as a mirror when not in use. It is the first mirror TV in LCD anywhere in the world, said D. Shivkumar, vice-president, consumer electronics at Philips India.																								Company officials said the high resolution and the pixel-plus technology used in the 30-inch TV justified its high price. In the audio-video range, Philips unveiled DVD 596, a hi-fi category (mini-audio system) for Rs 26,990 and a cheaper stand-alone DVD for Rs 9,990.																								While Philips consumer electronics division clocked a turnover of Rs 700 crore this fiscal, Shivkumar said, We aim at a strong double digit growth for fiscal 2004-05. Last year, the division had reported a 4-5 per cent growth. 
